            <title>[FELIX-4048] @Requires handler does not fail when no specification can be found</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4048</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The requires handler is designed to track services using their service interfaces (specification).&lt;br/&gt;
If no specification is found, there is no failure at deploy time, but nothing happen during execution.&lt;br/&gt;
that&apos;s a silent failure &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;iPOJO should throw an Exception and express the fact that the configuration is invalid&lt;/p&gt;</description>
